ce:section.ce:para:
Before investigating the DMFC performance of the membranes, mechanical, thermal stability were also studied. The strain-stress curves of the composite membranes and the pristine HBM membrane were compared in Fig. 5
                     . Mechanical strength of the GQD-HBM membrane is found to be significantly enhanced with a mechanical strength of 18.8 MPa, which is almost 80% increase compared to that of the pristine HBM membrane. For the GO-HBM membrane, although the hydrogen-binding interactions can enhance the tensile stress of the membrane while the elongation at break is strongly decrease due to the large-scale phase separation. At the same time, the composite membrane maintains excellent oxidative stability due to the good oxidative stability of GO and GQD (Table 1). According to the TG curves (Fig. 6
                     ), there is on significant weight loss until 280 °C for the composite membrane. The composite membrane still maintains great thermal stability.
